the first season was a masterpiece (my opinion is they should have stopped there), the second was worse but it was not a bad film, just that everything was too mundane..(but the characters were cool) 

all characters of the first two shows were FUCKED UP...that was their main charm...all were damaged goods....

here it looks that the maker couldn't realy decide how his cahracters should be....and they seem pulled in many directions but go into none...


I get the take on the metaphysical TIME IS A FLAT CIRCLE ..and that everything exists in a single moment, that NOTHING actually happens , and all is a clever concoted illusion...but you don't need eight fucking episodes to express that (however the film does express this point PERFECTLY tho)


the first season expressed that feeling also, but it expanded on the STRUGGLE of human beings within that state...there was ACTUAL DRAMA there ..although drama was not the point....there was emotion , depth of feeling , melancholy.....here there are only shallow attemps at emotions and zero depth...the moments that try to be profound are robbed of depth by a much too shallow and rushed presentation


none of the characters REALLY STRUGGLE..Although the film tries to trick the audience into beliving so...


to sum things up ..you watch eight episodes..only to come to the conclusion that nothing happened...too bad for the great crushing atmosphere...

Jacobs ladder had struggle...this feels half assed low budget to me ...even like a cheap ripoff....almost a waste of time
